	   <tr><td colspan=2>It is freezing.&nbsp;&nbsp;Biting winds and blinding snows have hampered my travels in Velious.  I am alone as I burrow into the bank of snow and try once more to wrap the worn bearskin tight about me.  Alas, though, I find my numbed fingers pulling the cold hard shield, the Aegis of Life.  Surely a wonderous gift, I do acknowledge, with its imbued powers giving me yet more understanding and ability at casting spells.  Yet, it is times like this that I miss the weight, comfort, and simplicity that humble cape provided.  Perhaps in the light of the new dawn I shall find a Blood Dire Wolf and take possession his harness.<br><br>Darkness has decended and even the fire grows dim as the wind continues to rage and the swirling snows makes keeping an alert guard up nigh impossible.  As I have learned I must due, I close my eyes to these simple worries.  Rodcefe Nif shall protect me as he sees fit, it has become that simple.<br><br>Yet I fear to close my eyes.  And I have succeeded for the last several nights by traveling and minor fights with the denizens of Velious that attack a weary traveler.  But tonight my body feels as much numbed by fatigue as by the cold.<br><br>"To keep me warm at night, my hero!"  Her voice was a pleasure, so light and airy that I can still not find the words to describe the sound and how it feels.  Her long lashes lowered as I could not help but stare at her, and her faced warmed with the blush of embarassment.  "Yes, my hero, I collect these kisses and remember them during my time of loniness."<br><br>My heart ached as I yearned to pull her close, yet I know she is far to perfect for one such as I to hold and taint.  So I stood, lost in grief and dispair, as she flittered to yet other heroes and stole her kisses.  So gracious and beautiful, I could find no fault in her.  She was like a butterfly going from flower to flower.  Too beautiful to be captured, too rare and precious to be constrained.  Sure there were those far greater than I that held her for a moment, their laughter ringing out together in mutual jests and teasings.  But always she stole her kiss and lifted freely from the clasping arms to gather yet another kiss from another joyous soul.  I know I can never hold her for I am too jealous.  But I shall ne'er forget the feel of the lips that lightly brushed mine nor the velvetness of her blushing cheek when I dared to touch her face.  Just as she will ever be free, I know I am forever bound to serve her.  I am empty yet I am full, I am content.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>A simple cleric of Rodcet Nif on Tholuxe Paells</td></tr>
