	   <tr><td colspan=2>Today I am sitting on a dock.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am in such deep thought I find little solace in fishing, which has ever brought me out of the deepest of feelings.  I have bought a lot of bait to figure this all out, yet I simply can not concentrate on my problem.  Aye, in fact, I can not seem to concentrate on anything ever since I saw her.<br><br>I dream far too much of her finely sculpted features.  Her elegant long nose.  Those delightfully inviting pointed ears.  Yet I have seen many a high elf maiden that has not affected me such as she has.  They are pretty and even some of them seem not to be so racially high minded as high elves tend to be.<br><br>I know she is physically weak, yet her mind is so fantastically strong.  She is both breathtaking in vision and in thought that I can think of nothing else!<br><br>I fear her too.  Aye fear her more than Nagafen or Vox, mighty dragons that they be!  Her presence makes me tremble and makes my tongue fumble the simplest of sentences!  I fear I am lost without her, yet to be with her I am lost to her charms.<br><br>Soon I shall meet her again, or maybe not.  I have to concentrate, yet I can not.  Do I flee her beauty and charm or be swallowed helplessly by her simplicity and grace?  Do I board the ship to Velious and thus as far as possible from her presence or sail the Maiden's Voyage to Butcherblock Mountains and thus stand in her consuming radiance?<br><br>Helplessly I struggle with my thoughts, the fishing pole long since stowed away and forgotten, as her pale blue eyes shine brightly in my memory and her soft lips curl with her tantalizing smile.<br><br>I need board the boat, yet which?<br>&nbsp;<br>A simple cleric of Rodcet Nif on Tholuxe Paells</td></tr>
