<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100564041313099></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100564041313099><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=46685&mid=100564041313099>A tailor's perspective.</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=46685&mid=100564041313099#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=46685><span id=Scholar>Laleldil</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>78 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 13th 3:33 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Will I pay 20pp for a HQ pelt? Sometimes, if I think the person selling it needs money and is relatively low level. Why? First of all, there is not a good market for 10-slot bags that are only 10% reducing and weight 3 stones. Why is that? Because I can go to Iceclad safely at nearly any level and purchase a 10 slot toolbox for 9pp that weighs only 3.5 stones and 0% wt. reducing. There then is no reason to expect any but the most foolish of players to pay 100pp, 80pp, or even 20pp, for a bank slot increasing bag. <br><br>How about its wt. reducing and carrying items? First it is only 10% wt. reducing. Should be enough said, but for those that have a few moments more than thinking capacity, evil eye bags are 8-slot 70% reducing and cost 300-350 pp. Herbalist bags are 25% and 6-slot. Many other containers can also be looted far more reducing then 10%. <br><br>Now let's couple some of this with the idea of many items that need to be stored that weigh 0.1 stone. You need the slots but don't even notice any weight reduction at all! And a master looter, porter, whatever, will be greatly encumbered filling a 10-slot bag with FS weapons or Brass Armor, hence will be walking to sell in WC or Highpass Hold Keep long before his slots are filled. <br><br>Recommendations: Carry the much lighter 0.8 stone 6-slot 10% wt. reducing bags until you can get your sewn evileye bag or herbalist pack or other quested, looted wt. reducing container. Use a cheap 10-slot deluxe toolbox or two for your many tiny wt. items and an 8-slot sewing bag for those infrequent giant-size items. Let's math it out if you need help here. 7x3=21 leaving 1 slot for a light source or other item that needs looting. This is filled with 10-slot bags. 4x0.8= 3.2 + 4 (sewing kit) + 2x3.5 = 7(toolboxs) =&gt;3.2+4+7=14.2 saving nearly 7 stones in weight. To make the 10% bags save you 7 stones you would need to carry 70 stones in your toolboxs and sewing kit! You still have 24 slots in the 4 6-slot bags that you could have put all that heavy stuff inside and still have the 10% wt reduction. <br><br>Moral: A fool and his money is soon parted. <br><br>So buy your sewing kit, kill spiderlings, make cords, kill bears and get LQ pelts and save your money. You will be richer in pp, talent, and satisfaction, and still carry more items than you can bear. Can't find any thing but those silly MQ and HQ pelts? Combine with a skinning knife in your sewing kit until LQ. Patiently save your pp to buy the evileye bag, or hehe, get some pleasure from looting your own. <br><br>Would I buy your pelts? Maybe, but not to make money, only to help you as you struggle to play untwinked. I personally know no one dumb enough to waste 100pp for a tailored backpack. Yes they might still exist, but I just do not feel comfortable about ripping other players off. Hehe I get ripped enough to know how it feels.<br><br>Postscript to above:&nbsp;&nbsp;Please save your HQ pelts for yourself.  Keep trying to make them whether you are trivial or not.  When you get one successfully made (always a possibility, though less probable at lower tailoring skills) replace the tool boxs you are carrying with your own 10-slot bags.  Just don't get rapidly encumbered by replacing the 6-slot bags unless you get a lot better than 10% reducing bags.  Even summoned bags of shamans and magicians (?) would be better than the 10-slots, though for obvious reasons risky as they *poof* if you go LD and can't get back on in time or the server crashs thus LOSING everything in them!<br> <br><br>&nbsp;<br>A simple cleric of Rodcet Nif on Tholuxe Paells</td></tr>
