ing.  You mezzed a mob?  Mind blur.  Demand the mob gets rooted! Don't allow the mob's filthy weapon to soil your pretty dress, er robe!<br><br>Please help the cleric.  Watch the aggro.  Careful demanding buffs then not waiting.  Kill that silly puppy that keeps me from staying on my lazy *&&.  Else go bring me, or take me to get some armor with clickable effects!<br><br>If you are reading cleric is 00m and you, the mighty warrior has just recieved a greatHeal.  For pete's sake do not go wading back into the fray!  You got the greater healing only because that is all I have left!  Da mob wipes that out in seconds, far sooner than I can med it back! Please, Please let that other warrior keep aggro even though he is only two red bubbles left alive!  Maybe the ranger has some mana and can heal you a little, I DO NOT!  Let me med to get whatever slight mana I can to put on the other warrior!  If your near dead standing corpse is within range, that mob is going to kill you!  It is even better if I get up and start swinging my silly little club then for you to taunt him with your near corpse condition.  And believe me I am no battle cleric!  But I do have 1.5k or so hp more than you do now and not all that bad at defense! (188)<br><br>/rant off<br><br>Sorry lost three today and mad as heck!  Puppy would not let me sit, warriors playing too much tag with aggro, no enchanter and bard trying to help keep warriors alive out of mana song range, not that I was able to sit and enjoy the music!  We owned that right moat and basement pulls for a long while!  We were a great group.  Bard was enchanter equivalent to above, wizard the ranger.  Still awed watching Cronchoker keeping mob busy and not getting too hurt!  One great... no fantastic Wizard!<br><br>Laleldil <br>&nbsp;<br>A simple cleric of Rodcet Nif on Tholuxe Paells</td></tr>
