	   <tr><td colspan=2>To the noble cleric Laleldil,<br><br>I fear that you have taught me humility.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am only a cleric of 40 seasons, and I would never think to ask for assistance on how to become a better cleric.  I always trusted that Tunare herself would guide me and teach me what I must know, but you have shown me the arrogance of my thoughts.<br><br>I know that I am of the Koada Dal, and that we do tend to be a people quite confident of our place in the world.  I only hope that I can learn from your own quest for wisdom.<br><br>May the gods grant you the wisdom you seek.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Icewind Novastorm<br>Koada Dal Cleric of Tunare<br>&lt;&lt;Mith Marr&gt;&gt;</td></tr>
