	   <tr><td colspan=2>Not sure that anyone will ever read this but I guess this is asgood as spot as anywhere to put this.<br><br>I an a level 49 Cleric on Tholuxe Paells with a wisdom of 180 and am human.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am presently in a guild called Order of Green Knights which is a small guild with perhaps a different outlook on Norrathe and environs then some other guilds.  Not to start any discussions on what guild is better or any other flames, I do not wish to leave my guild.<br><br>However since my guild is young and will be slow to mature to the ability to do planar raids and epic proportion raids, I would like to find a way to go on various outings that will teach me the better ways of being a cleric and also the methods and other aspects that need attention for a guild to start these endeavors.<br><br>I have followed the links here on Allakhazam's page and found the Tholuxe Paells Server and its forum.  I have perused the general discussions pages for quite some time and various other pages and unfortunately this server seems rift with flames and animosity at the high end of the game.  I am sure that this is not enveloping all high end players or even most of the players in the variuous guilds, yet in the general discussions page, threads become unbearably long with flames that have nothing to do with the original intent of the post, or at least as I see it.<br><br>Obviously I am not qualified to even come close to having a working relationship with alot of these people, however I have bumped into one or two of them during the game and have had no problems with them and at least one of them has helped me out in Karnor's Castle.<br><br>This I hope has shown that my question I am about to ask needs not be answered in flames or other than helpful manners.  Please if you need to flame someone, something, or even me, please go to the server site, a flame page, or just email me at laleldil@qtm.net.  Thank you.<br><br>I would like to be 'adopted', so to speak, by another guild that would be willing to help teach me the ways that would be most benefical to my guild.  I would, of course, be willing to follow all the adopting guild's requisites except to leave my guild.  I do not have naything of real value as evidenced by my low wisdom and few funds, yet I would attempt to follow your guild's customs to the best of my ability that do not conflict with the Charter and spirit of my own present guild.<br><br>Things that I would like to learn are how to be an excellent cleric, what is the way raids are run and executed, and anything else the adopting guild would think would help me help my guild mates.  I am not an officer of the guild that I am in, yet I am seeking this assistance on my own, so do not wish this message to anyway tarnish my guild's reputation.  It is a noble guild of friends that I hold dear.<br><br>Again please no flames or cuts and slams to other guilds or other individuals.  Any positive and teaching postings to this journal would be and will be read and heeded to the best of my ability with the gratuitousness befitting a Knight of the Green Order.<br><br>Thank you for your presence and thoughtfulness<br><br>Laleldil Tremulous<br>a 49 cleric in search of learning and wisdom<br>&nbsp;<br>A simple cleric of Rodcet Nif on Tholuxe Paells</td></tr>
